The paper focuses on the usage and attribution of code snippets from Stack Overflow in public GitHub projects, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The paper also discusses legal and licensing issues related to the use of code snippets, which could be relevant to programming languages (cs.PL), cybernetics (cs.CY), cryptography (cs.CR), and social and information networks (cs.SI) sub-categories.
